Tech & tooling
- Framework: Next.js 14 (App Router, src/app).
- Language: TypeScript.
- Styling: Tailwind CSS (+ tailwind.config).
- Icons: lucide-react.
- Animations: Framer Motion (subtle, premium feel).
- Package manager: npm (use `npm ci` in CI/Builder).
- Node: 20.x (match Vercel).

Structure & paths
- Keep the App Router in `src/app`.
- Real pages are under `src/app/(tabs)/{meu-dia,cuidar,descobrir,eu360}`.
- `components/` holds shared UI (`components/ui`) and features (`components/features`).
- Path alias is `@/*` (do NOT change). Don’t duplicate or move pages out of `src/app`.

Dev server & scripts
- Dev server runs on http://localhost:3001.
- `scripts.dev` must be `next dev -p 3001`.
- When Builder needs deps, run `npm ci` (not `npm install`). If lockfile diverges, allow `--no-frozen-lockfile` in Builder and commit the updated `package-lock.json`.

Branching & PRs
- Default working branch: `main`.
- Open PRs **from `main`** (or short-lived `builder/*` feature branches) **into `main`**.
- Mark PRs as **Draft** by default.
- Use Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`).
- Do not change repository or create new ones.

Design guidelines
- Premium look: soft shadows, rounded corners, smooth micro-interactions.
- Brand palette: Primary #ff005e; Secondary #ffd8e6.
- Mobile-first + a11y (focus states, readable contrast).

What NOT to change
- Don’t rename packages arbitrarily.
- Don’t alter `@/*` alias or ports (keep 3001 for Builder dev).
- Don’t hardcode secrets; use env vars (public only as `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` in Builder).
- Don’t introduce breaking changes to API routes or Next config (use ESM, `next.config.mjs`).

